invite.Description: Invite link for Roki to join your server.

channelinfo.Description: Shows information about the current channel/mentioned channel.

ping.Description: Gets current ping to Discord's servers

commands.Description: List all of the bot's commands and their aliases from a module. You can either specify the full/the first few letters of the module name.

h.Description: Either shows a help for a single Aliases,/DMs you help link if no parameters are specified.

time.Description: Shows the current date and time for the specified location. Also includes date and time in local culture if exists.

image.Description: Searches Google Images with the specified query, returns first result.

randomimage.Description: Searches Google Images with the specified query, returns a random result.

movie.Description: Searches omdb with the specified query, returns first result.

weather.Description: Looks up weather of specified city using Dark Sky's api.

urbandict.Description: Searches urban dictionary for with the specified query.

addquote.Description: Adds a new quote with the specified name and message.

showquote.Description: Shows a random quote with a specified name

quotesearch.Description: Shows a random quote for a keyword that contains any text specified in the search.

quoteid.Description: Displays the quote with the specified ID number. Quote ID numbers can be found by typing `{0}liqu [num]` where `[num]` is a number of a page which contains 15 quotes.

quotedelete.Description: Deletes a quote with the specified Keyword. You have to be either server Administrator/the creator of the quote to delete it.

quotedeleteid.Description: Deletes a quote with the specified ID. You have to be either server Administrator/the creator of the quote to delete it.

listquotes.Description: Lists all quotes on the server ordered alphabetically. 15 Per page.

listquotesid.Description: Lists all quotes on the server ordered by creation date. 15 Per page.

textoimage.Description: Returns an image showing the specified mathematical formula, using the TeX language.

pokedex.Description: Returns a short summary of the specified Pok√©mon.

ability.Description: Returns the description of the specified ability.

move.Description: Returns the description of the specified move.

item.Description: Returns the description of the specified item.

pins.Description: Returns the latest pin in the current channel.

xkcd.Description: Returns the specified xkcd comic, if no comic is specified, latest comic is shown.

queue.Description: Searches and plays the query for the specified song,/plays the url provided. If the url is a playlist, it adds all tracks in the playlist into the queue. Must be in a voice channel.

play.Description: Plays a specific track # in the queue.

autoplay.Description: Enables/Disables autoplay for the current player. Automatically plays a related track to the last track played. Mutually exclusive with loop (i.e. only one can be enabled). Must be in a voice channel.

queueloop.Description: Enables/Disables loop for the current player. Restarts the player queue from the beginning. Mutually exclusive with autoplay (i.e. only one can be enabled). Must be in a voice channel.

pause.Description: Pauses the current track playing. Must be in a voice channel.

resume.Description: Un-pauses the current paused track. Must be in a voice channel.

destroy.Description: Stops the bot from playing music. Must be in a voice channel.

volume.Description: Sets the volume for the music player. Between 0-100. Must be in a voice channel

listqueue.Description: Shows the current track queue (10 tracks per page).

songremove.Description: Removes the specified track in the queue.

songseek.Description: Seeks the given number of seconds forward in the current track.

twitter.Description: Returns the latest tweets by the specified user.

twittersearch.Description: Searches twitter with the specified query, and returns the top 5 results.

anime.Description: Returns top 5 anime results provided from the query.

experience.Description: Shows the current XP and Level of the current user. Optional: mention another user to see their XP and Level.

xpleaderboard.Description: Shows the current xp leaderboard, you can specify the page, default is the top 9.

xpnotification.Description: Sets the preferred location of xp level up notifications (Server, Dm,/None).

pick.Description: Picks up all the currency dropped in the current channel.

leaderboard.Description: Shows the current currency leaderboard. you can specify the page, default is the top 9.

drop.Description: Drops the specified number of currency, default is 1. Must have enough in your balance to drop.

betflip.Description: Bet to guess result if heads/tails. Guessing correctly awards you currency.

give.Description: Transfers currency to the specified user, optionally with a message. Must have sufficient balance.

cash.Description: Shows how much cash the user has.

investing.Description: Shows how much currency in the Investing Account.

betroll.Description: Bet to roll a dice. Rolling over 70 yields x2.5, over 90 yields x4, and 100 yields x10.

currencytransactions.Description: Shows your currency transactions on the specified page.

betflipmulti.Description: Bet to guess multiple coin flips. You need to bet at least twice the amount of guesses in stones. Needs 3/4 to be correct. The more correct guess rewards more currency. (amount * correct ^ 1.1)

betpokemongame.Description: Bet on an AI vs AI game of pokemon. Default is Generation 8 (Available Generations: 4-8). If guessed winner correctly, win stones.

betpokemonreplay.Description: Gets the replay of a bet pokemon game.

trivia.Description: Starts a new 10 question trivia game with optional category (use `{0}tc` to check categories). Default is all categories. Awards currency based on difficulty. Needs at least 60% to get rewards.

store.Description: Shows the Stone store. 9 items per page./specify specific name/id to see that item.

buy.Description: Buy an item from the store using its name/id, must specify amount/all

mute.Description: Mutes the specified user (Prevents them from speaking in voice). Must be a moderator/have an available power (Consumes the power).

block.Description: Blocks the specified user (Prevents them from typing in chat). Must be a moderator/have an available power (Consumes the power).

timeout.Description: Times out the specified user (Prevents them from typing and speaking). Must be a moderator/have an available power (Consumes the power). Does not stack with `.mute` and `.block`.

inventory.Description: Shows the items in your inventory

stocknews.Description: Shows the current news about the specified company

stockcompany.Description: Shows details about the specified company

stockprice.Description: Shows the current price of the stock for the specified company

stockbuy.Description: Purchase shares of a company. Funds are taken from investing account

stocksell.Description: Sells shares of a company. Funds are deposited into your investing account

transfer.Description: Transfers currency the specified amount of currency to or from your (cash/investing) account.

userdetails.Description: Shows the users userid, username, discriminator, and avatar id

events.Description: Create, edit, show events in the current server.

uwu.Description: UwUizes the message. If no message is provided, UwUizes the previous message in the channel.

jeopardy.Description:
Starts a Jeopardy! game in the current channel. Choose a price from the categories, and give the correct answer to win.
If a game is active in the current channel, the current question will be sent again.

jeopardyleaderboard.Description: Shows the score leaderboard for the current Jeopardy! game.

jeopardystop.Description: Stops current Jeopardy! game after the current question.

jeopardyvote.Description: Votes to skip the current question. Can vote if you have a score in the current game. Voting opens 12 seconds after clue is shown.

wikipedia.Description: Searches Wikipedia for an article. Shows most relevant article. Can add `-q` to end of Aliases show top 5 results instead.

ask.Description: Asks roki a question. Uses Wolfram|Alpha to get answers.
Usage: {0}ask what is the tallest building in the world

xprewards.Description: Shows the XP rewards for the current server. Optional: specify page number, show reward id

notsafeforwork.Description: Sends random NSFW/Porn image. Requires NSFW Channel.

ass.Description: Sends random image of asses. Requires NSFW Channel.

boobs.Description: Sends random image of boobs. Requires NSFW Channel.

cosplay.Description: Sends random image of cosplays. Requires NSFW Channel.

hentai.Description: Sends random image of hentai. Requires NSFW Channel.

mild.Description: Sends random mild nsfw/sfw image. Requires NSFW Channel.

nsfwgifs.Description: Sends random NSFW/Porn gif. Requires NSFW Channel.

trans.Description: Sends random image of trans/traps. Requires NSFW Channel.

chesschallenge.Description: Challenge a user to a chess game by mentioning them.

kick.Description: Kick a user from the server.

ban.Description: Ban a user from the server.

prune.Description: Deletes up to the specified number of messages of the mentioned user (not guaranteed to delete the exact specified number). Only searches up to the past 500 total messages.
